And I'm Georgie. If you've heard about Meet Free Mondays or Veganiry, you probably know about a trend which an increasing number of people are trying to reduce or even stop eating meat.

4
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
This is often for health, animal welfare, or environmental reasons.

5
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:33.000
Instead, people are getting their daily amount of protein through plant-based alternatives.

6
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:41.000
Meet Free sausages and burgers made using ingredients like soy, tofu, or fungi, as well as temper, beans or nuts.

7
00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Have you tried any of these plant-based meat or turnative Georgie?

8
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:53.000
Yes, I have. I have lots of vegetarian friends, so I've been to veggie barbecues and have tried the plant-based sausages and burgers.

9
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.000
I quite like them, as long as they're covered in sauce. What about you?

10
00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Yeah, I think I agree. They're fine. There's a reason for them, but I'm not sure there is good as the real thing.

11
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:12.000
Now, with process meat being linked to diseases like diabetes and cancer, most doctors agree that plant-based options are healthier.

12
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:19.000
But some people are worried about how plant-based alternatives are made, including radio-list-net-gram-gluever,

13
00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:23.000
who ask this question to BBC Radio 4 programme sliced bread.

14
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:31.000
My question is, looking at these vegetable sausages, how they are processed, full of other tips and flare-rings and colourings,

15
00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:34.000
are they any healthier than a pork sausage?

16
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:40.000
In this episode, we'll be finding out where the plant-based foods really are a healthier alternative to meat.

17
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
And as usual, we'll be learning some useful new words and phrases.

